  "comments": "<p>UV activity:<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/64f2289f7d46e.png\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/64f2289f7d46e.png\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© gyoschak</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668fb605113c.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668fb605113c.jpg\"></a></p><p>© Kiet Tran</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">Security thread:</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">Solid, only visible under a backlight with the inscription of “50 ГРН” repeated three times as well as the national emblem.</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668fb816d2ac.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668fb816d2ac.jpg\"></a></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">© Kiet Tran</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">The denomination “50” is printed in colour shifting ink, changes colour from purple to gold when note is tilted:</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668fbea822a3.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668fbea822a3.jpg\"></a><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668fbefc19f0.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668fbefc19f0.jpg\"></a></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">© Kiet Tran</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\"><br><br>Volodymyr Semenovych Stelmakh was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2000 until 2002 and from 2004 until 2010<br>Serhiy Leonidovych Tihipko was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2002 until 2004<br>Serhiy Hennadiiovych Arbuzov was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2010 until 2012<br>Ihor Viacheslavovych Sorkin was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2013 until 2014<br>Stepan Kubiv was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine in 2014<br>Valeriya Oleksiivna Hontareva was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2014 until May 11, 2017</p>",
